<item>
            <title>[CXF-2302] HTTP continuations are not working correctly if keep-alives are on</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2302</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
The HTTP continuations are using the jetty continuation isNew method to see if it&apos;s &quot;new&quot;.  However, that method is really not named correctly as it&apos;s &quot;new per connection&quot; not &quot;per request&quot;.  Thus, with keep alives, the continuation is reused and CXF state gets confused.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
